			"relation": "progression"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "In this paper , we focus on labeling full argument spans of discourse connectives in the Penn Discourse Treebank ( PDTB ) . <S>",
			"relation": "bg-goal"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Previous studies cast this task as a linear tagging or subtree extraction problem . <S>",
			"relation": "bg-compare"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "In this paper , we propose a novel constituent-based approach to argument labeling , ",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "which integrates the advantages of both linear tagging and subtree extraction . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "In particular , the proposed approach unifies intra- and inter-sentence cases ",
			"relation": "elab-aspect"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "by treating the immediately preceding sentence as a special constituent . <S>",
			"relation": "manner-means"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 5,
			"text": "Besides , a joint inference mechanism is introduced ",
			"relation": "elab-aspect"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "to incorporate global information across arguments into our constituent-based approach ",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
